Rating: 4
As many people mentioned, this soup is pretty bland before seasoning. I added quite a bit of salt and pepper, then a bunch of stuff from the spice rack. The best addition was a healthy dose of cayenne; it gave a heat that paired really well with the sweet corn. Also seasoned salt, garlic powder, and chili powder. If it still tastes bland, just keep adding! End result was fantastic.

