Rating: 3
I made this recipe with what I had in my kitchen, which means I used frozen corn, milk, chicken stock and cilantro. Despite all those modifications, it was still very good, although a little thin (my fault for substituting milk for cream I suppose). It was absolutely beautiful too, and filling enough to serve as a main dish. Next time, I'll probably puree some of the potatoes before I add the other vegetables to compensate for the milk/cream substitution, because I don't really like fatty soups.

